Headline: Data migration wizard
Text: This is great! I've worked with several people doing data migrations recommending that if the data shouldn't change (e.g. historical records, legal and compliance), then use an archive solution; if the data should change (open tickets, active changes, etc.), then think about copying to new system. Great to get some best practices around the latter half!
Bio: My company, Synapse Software, specializes in data archive, migration, and automation solutions built on top of our no-code Cortex platform. Originally, we started by archiving Cherwell data and migrating it to systems like Halo and InvGate, but now have support for archiving several systems and integrating with many other modern ITSM systems, including ServiceNow.
